## Batch Offer Generation Endpoint

### Request

```
POST /v1/offers/batch
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### Request Body

```json
{
  "profile_ids": ["<master_customer_id>", "..."],
  "product_types": ["<ProductType>", "..."]
}
```

| Field           | Type            | Required | Default           | Description                                                                       |
|-----------------|-----------------|----------|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `profile_ids`   | Array\<String\> | **Yes**  | —                 | One or more `master_customer_id` values. Maximum 500 per request.                 |
| `product_types` | Array\<Enum\>   | No       | `["recommended"]` | Filter offers to the specified product categories. See [Product Types](#product-types). |

#### Product Types

| Value          | Description                                      |
|----------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `recommended`      | **(Default)** System-selected best-fit products  |
| `personal_loans`   | Personal loans                                   |
| `student_loans`    | Student loans                                    |
| `auto_loans`       | Auto loans                                       |
| `auto_insurance`   | Auto insurance                                   |
| `home_insurance`   | Home insurance                                   |
| `credit_cards`     | Credit card products                             |
| `mortgage`         | Home mortgage products                           |
| `cds`              | Certificates of deposit                          |
| `savings`          | Savings accounts                                 |
| `checking`         | Checking accounts                                |
| `home_equity`      | Home equity loans / HELOCs                       |

**Example Request:**

```json
{
  "profile_ids": ["a1b2c3d4-0001", "a1b2c3d4-0002"],
  "product_types": ["credit_cards", "personal_loans"]
}
```

---

### Response Envelope

**HTTP 200 OK**

```json
{
  "results": [
    {
      "master_customer_id": "a1b2c3d4-0001",
      "status": "success",
      "offers": [ ... ]
    }
  ],
  "summary": {
    "total_requested": 1,
    "total_succeeded": 1,
    "total_failed": 0
  }
}
```

| Field                             | Type    | Description                                                                              |
|-----------------------------------|---------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `results`                         | Array   | One entry per `profile_id` in the request, in the same order.                           |
| `results[].master_customer_id`    | String  | The profile ID from the request.                                                         |
| `results[].status`                | Enum    | `success` or `error`                                                                     |
| `results[].offers`                | Array   | Array of offer objects. Empty array if no offers qualify. Schema varies by `product_type`. |
| `results[].error`                 | Object  | Present only when `status` is `error`. Contains `code` and `message`.                   |
| `summary.total_requested`         | Integer | Number of profile IDs in the request.                                                    |
| `summary.total_succeeded`         | Integer | Number of profiles for which offers were generated (including empty sets).               |
| `summary.total_failed`            | Integer | Number of profiles that returned an error.                                               |

Each offer in `results[].offers` contains a common envelope plus a `details` object whose schema depends on `product_type`:

```json
{
  "offer_id": "string",
  "product_type": "credit_cards | personal_loans | student_loans | auto_loans | auto_insurance | home_insurance | mortgage | home_equity | savings | checking | mma | cds",
  "details": { ... }
}
```

| Field           | Type    | Description                                                                   |
|-----------------|---------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `offer_id`      | String  | Unique identifier for this offer instance.                                    |
| `product_type`  | Enum    | The product category.                                                         |
| `details`       | Object  | Product-specific fields. See schemas below.                                   |

