## Error Responses

| HTTP Status | Code                    | Description                                                                 |
|-------------|-------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `400`       | `INVALID_REQUEST`       | Request body is malformed or fails validation (e.g., empty `profile_ids`). |
| `400`       | `INVALID_PRODUCT_TYPE`  | One or more values in `product_types` are not recognized.                  |
| `400`       | `BATCH_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`  | More than 500 profile IDs submitted in a single request.                   |
| `401`       | `UNAUTHORIZED`          | Missing or invalid Bearer token.                                            |
| `404`       | `PROFILE_NOT_FOUND`     | Per-profile error when a `master_customer_id` does not exist in the DB.    |
| `422`       | `INSUFFICIENT_DATA`     | Per-profile error when mandatory fields are missing to generate any offer. |
| `429`       | `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED`   | Too many requests. Retry after the duration in the `Retry-After` header.   |
| `500`       | `INTERNAL_ERROR`        | Unexpected server error. Safe to retry.                                     |

**Example 400 Response:**

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "INVALID_REQUEST",
    "message": "profile_ids must contain at least one entry."
  }
}
```

