## Security Considerations

| Concern                    | Mitigation                                                                                       |
|----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| PII at rest                | `last_4_ssn` and `email` encrypted at rest using AES-256. Database-level encryption enabled.     |
| PII in transit             | All SFTP transfers use SSH. All API traffic over TLS 1.2+.                                       |
| Authentication             | API requires Bearer token (OAuth 2.0 client credentials flow recommended).                       |
| SFTP access control        | Partner authenticates with SSH key pair. Each partner has an isolated SFTP directory.            |
| Sensitive data in logs     | `last_4_ssn` must be masked/excluded from all log output. Emails should be masked in debug logs. |
| Input validation           | All CSV fields validated before DB write. API request body schema-validated before processing.   |
| Rate limiting              | Offer endpoint rate-limited per API key. Limits returned in `X-RateLimit-*` response headers.    |

